    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/1147#issuecomment-4624378065\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/1147\">issue #1147</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Bitcasts are necessary due to CLIF's design and that is not going to change in the foreseeable future. We have and use the tools to see through these in lowering rules when it makes sense. If there is any bad codegen due to the lack of using those tooles in lowering rules, then we should file targeted issues for those cases. Closing this issue.</p>\n</blockquote>",
